 SELinux
 /etc/selinux/Config
 Parameters - changing SELinux Modes at Boot Times
 enforcing=0 starts the system in permissive mode - preferred method
 selinux=0 causes autorelabel on next reboot
 autorelabel=1 same as touch /.autorelabel ; reboot

 Problem = selinux is preventing httpd to start
 confirm by setenforce 0 then starting httpd
 grep httpd /var/log/messages - it gives solution too
 solution was =
 ausearch -c 'httpd' --raw | audit2allow -M my-httpd
 To make this policy package active, execute
# semodule -i my-httpd.pp
recheck
grep httpd /var/log/messages - it gives solution too
change context of http directory
# semanage fcontext -a -t httpd_sys_content_t "web/(/.*)?"
retorecon -Rv /web
systemctl restart httpd
tail -100 /var/log/messages | less